SIMPLE: gazetteer
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Gazetteer
<hw>Gaz`et*teer"</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Cf. F.
<ets>gazetier</ets>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>A writer of news, or an
officer appointed to publish news by authority.</def>
<rj><au>Johnson.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>A newspaper; a gazette.</def> <mark>[Obs.]</mark>
<rj><au>Burke.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <def>A geographical dictionary; a book giving the names
and descriptions, etc., of many places.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>4.</sn> <def>An alphabetical descriptive list of
anything.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Gazingstock</ent>⟦br⟧
